{"lemma":"إِمْرَةٌ","slug":"إِمْرَةٌ","root":"#.م.ر","root_slug":"_-م-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/_-م-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1205","n1206","n1207","n1216","n1217","n1218","n1226","n1227","n1228","n38363"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A5%D9%90%D9%85%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1205","headword_ar":"اَمَرَهُ","root":"Amd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An extreme term, limit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"point, reached,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attained."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n1206","headword_ar":"اَمَرَهُ","root":"Amr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, &c.,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amorN","text_ar":"اَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imaArN","text_ar":"اـِمَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, L, K,) which latter, however, is disapproved by MF, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iymaArN","text_ar":"اـِيمَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. therewith, (K,) but this also is disapproved by MF, and deemed by him strange, [being by rule the inf. n. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=marahu","text_ar":"ا=مَرَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", respecting which see what follows,] (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=mirapN","text_ar":"ا=مِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) which is one of the inf. ns. [or quasiinf. ns.] of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEilapN","text_ar":"فَاعِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAfiyapN","text_ar":"عَافِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAqibapN","text_ar":"عَاقِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He commanded him; ordered him; bade him; enjoined him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the inf. n. signifying the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahoYN","text_ar":"نَهْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=mrhu","text_ar":"ا=مرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kr, M, K,) mentioned by A'Obeyd also as a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^marahu","text_ar":"امَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) but A'Obeyd says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=marotuhu","text_ar":"ا=مَرْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amrotuhu","text_ar":"اَمرْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are syn. [in a sense different from that explained above, i. e.] as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kav~arotuhu","text_ar":"كَثَّرْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amarahu bihi","text_ar":"اَمَرَهُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amarahu A_iy~aAhu","text_ar":"اَمَرَهُ اـِيَّاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", suppressing the prep., (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He commanded, ordered, bade,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enjoined, him to do it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^marotuka A^ano tafoEala","text_ar":"امَرْتُكَ اَنْ تَفْعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"litafoEala","text_ar":"لِتَفْعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA^no tafoEala","text_ar":"بِانْ تَفْعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I commanded, ordered, bade,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enjoined, thee to do"},{"kind":"text","text":"[such a thing]. (M.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amarahu bika*aA","text_ar":"اَمَرَهُ بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He commanded him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ordered him, to make use of such a thing; or the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence, in a trad.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^umirotu biAls~iwaAki","text_ar":"اُمِرْتُ بِالسِّوَاكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have been commanded to make use of the tooth-stick"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (El-Jámi' es- Sagheer.) [And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He enjoined him such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as, for instance, patience.] The imperative of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amara","text_ar":"اَمَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muro","text_ar":"مُرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aw^omuro","text_ar":"اوْمُرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which also occurs [with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa","text_ar":"وَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w^","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"when the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pronounced with damm]: (M:) but [generally] when it is not preceded by a conjunction, (Msb,) i. e., by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa","text_ar":"وَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fa","text_ar":"فَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,) you suppress the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e. the radical"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", and with it the conjunctive"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"preceding it,] contr. to rule, and say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murohu bika*aA","text_ar":"مُرْهُ بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Command,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"order,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enjoin, thou him to do such a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; like as you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kulo","text_ar":"كُلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu*o","text_ar":"خُذْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": when, however, it is preceded by a conjunction, the practice commonly obtaining is, to restore the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA^omuro bika*aA","text_ar":"وَاْمُرْ بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with analogy, and thus to say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amuro bika*aA","text_ar":"اَمُرْ بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b2-  [You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amara bihi faqutila","text_ar":"اَمَرَ بِهِ فَقُتِلَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave an order respecting him, and accordingly he was slain."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amara lahu bika*aA","text_ar":"اَمَرَ لَهُ بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ordered that such a thing should be done, or given, to him"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  In the Kur [xvii. 17],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaronaA mutorafiyhaA fafasaquwA fiyhaA","text_ar":"اَمَرْنَا مُتْرَفِيهَا فَفَسَقُوا فِيهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", so accord. to most of the readers, (T, &c.,) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We commanded"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its luxurious inhabitants"},{"kind":"text","text":"] to obey,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but they transgressed therein,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"departed from the right way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disobeyed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, T, S, &c.:) so says Aboo-Is-hák; adding that, although one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amartu zayodFA faDaraba EamorFA","text_ar":"اَمَرتُ زَيْدًا فَضَرَبَ عَمْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I commanded Zeyd to beat 'Amr, and he beat him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"yet one also says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amarotuka faEaSayotaniY","text_ar":"اَمَرْتُكَ فَعَصَيْتَنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I commanded thee, but thou disobeyedst me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or, accord. to some, the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We multiplied its luxurious inhabitants;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T;) and this is agreeable with another reading, namely, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=maronaA","text_ar":"ا=مَرْنَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and a reading of El-Hasan, namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amironaA","text_ar":"اَمِرْنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalimonaA","text_ar":"عَلِمْنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", may be a dial. var., of the same signification: (M:) see 4, in two places: or it may be from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_imaArapu","text_ar":"الاـِمَارَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, TA;) [in which case it seems that we should read ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^am~aronaA","text_ar":"اَمَّرْنَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or, perhaps,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaronaA","text_ar":"اَمَرْنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 2:] Abu-l-'Áliyeh reads ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^am~aronaA","text_ar":"اَمَّرْنَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and this is agreeable with the explanation of I'Ab, who says that the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We made its chiefs to have authority, power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dominion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amarahu","text_ar":"اَمَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He commanded, ordered, bade,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enjoined, him to do that which it behooved him to do."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He counselled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"advised, him"},{"kind":"text","text":".] One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muroniY","text_ar":"مُرْنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Counsel thou me; advise thou me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amara biAqotinaASK","text_ar":"اَمَرَ بِاقْتِنَاصٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said"},{"kind":"page_break","n":96},{"kind":"text","text":"of a wild animal, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rendered"},{"kind":"text","text":"the beholder"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desirous of capturing"},{"kind":"text","text":"him. (M.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amara","text_ar":"اَمَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As, Fr, Th, T, S, M, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amura","text_ar":"اَمُرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, IKtt, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amira","text_ar":"اَمِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K, and several other authorities; but by some this is disallowed; TA;) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amorN","text_ar":"اَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imorapN","text_ar":"اـِمْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imaArapN","text_ar":"اـِمَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (As, T, S;) or the second is a simple subst.; (K;) or perhaps it is meant in the S that this and the third are quasi-inf. ns.; (MF;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"held, command; he presided as a commander, governor, lord, prince,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"king;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amiyr","text_ar":"اَمِير"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (As, T, S;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqawomi","text_ar":"القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over the people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, * Msb, K.) [See also 5.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amara fulaAnN waA^umira Ealayohi","text_ar":"اَمَرَ فُلَانٌ وَاُمِرَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elyh","text_ar":"عليه"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wA^um~ira","text_ar":"واُمِّرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in different copies of the S,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one has held command and been commanded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said of one who has been a commander, or governor, after having been a subject of a commander, or governor; meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one is a person of experience;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who has been tried,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proved and strengthened, by experience."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amarahu","text_ar":"اَمَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=marahu","text_ar":"ا=مَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4.       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amira","text_ar":"اَمِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amarN","text_ar":"اَمَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amorap","text_ar":"اَمْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K, TA; the latter written in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aamorap","text_ar":"اَمْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^mura","text_ar":"امُرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IKtt;) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, M, Msb, or a man's property, or camels or the like, Abu-l-Hasan and S, and a people, T, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"multiplied;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became many,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, Msb, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became complete."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b2-  And the former, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His beasts multiplied;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became many;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) [as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=mr","text_ar":"ا=مر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for you say,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuw fulaAnK","text_ar":"بَنُو فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=mr","text_ar":"ا=مر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iymaArN","text_ar":"اـِيمَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The property,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, of the sons of such a one multiplied;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became many,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)       -A5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amira AlA^amoru","text_ar":"اَمِرَ الاَمْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Akh, S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amarN","text_ar":"اَمَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Akh, S,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e., a man's affair, or case, Akh, S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became severe, distressful, grievous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"afflictive."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Akh, S, K.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","Msb","K","L","TA","Kr","As","Fr","Th","Akh"]},{"entry_id":"n1207","headword_ar":"امّرهُ","root":"Amr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA^omiyrN","text_ar":"تَاْمِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appointed him, commander, governor, lord, prince,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"king."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Mgh, Msb.) [And it seems to be indicated in the S that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amarahu","text_ar":"اَمَرَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", without teshdeed, signifies the same.] See 1, in three places. You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~iraEalayonaA","text_ar":"اُمِّرَعَلَيْنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appointed, commander,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over us."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He appointed him judge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"umpire."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^m~r AlqanaApa","text_ar":"امّر القَنَاةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He affixed a spear-head to the cane"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spear."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M.) [See also the pass. part. n., below.] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^m~rA^amaArapK","text_ar":"امّراَمَارَةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a thing]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark, to show the way."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.)"}],"source_refs":["A","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n1216","headword_ar":"اَمْرَةٌ","root":"Amr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single command, order, bidding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"injunction:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laka EalaY~a A^amorapN muTaAEapN","text_ar":"لَكَ عَلَىَّ اَمْرَةٌ مُطَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast authority to give me one command, order, bidding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"injunction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which shall be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obeyed"},{"kind":"text","text":"by me. (S, M, * A, Msb, K.) You should not say, [in this sense,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imorapN","text_ar":"اـِمْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr. (T, S.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imorapN","text_ar":"اـِمْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n1217","headword_ar":"اـِمْرَةٌ","root":"Amr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amara","text_ar":"اَمَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Possession of command;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"office,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"authority, of a commander, governor, lord, prince,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"king;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, * Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imaArapN","text_ar":"اـِمَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaArapN","text_ar":"اَمَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, K;) but this last is by some disallowed, and is said in the Fs and its Expositions to be unknown. (MF.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEal~aka sA='a toka A_imorapu Aboni Eam~ika","text_ar":"لَعَلَّكَ سا=ءَ تْكَ اـِمْرَةُ ابْنِ عَمِّكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Perhaps thy paternal uncle's son's possession of command hath displeased thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [And hence, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Increase,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also other forms mentioned in what follows.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY wajohi","text_ar":"فِى وَجْهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAlika taEorifu A_imoratahu","text_ar":"مَالِكَ تَعْرِفُ اـِمْرَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In the face of thy property,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning such as consists in camels or the like, and also money,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thou knowest its increase and abundance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its expense:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_im~aratahu","text_ar":"اـِمَّرَتَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_im~ratahu","text_ar":"اـِمّرَتَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which latter is a dial. var. of weak authority, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^am~aratahu","text_ar":"اَمَّرَتَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its increase and abundance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_im~aratahu","text_ar":"اـِمَّرَتَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its prosperous state;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaAratahu","text_ar":"اَمَارَتَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amoratahu","text_ar":"اَمْرَتَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ibn-Buzurj:) accord. to AHeyth, who reads ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuEorafu A_im~aratuhu","text_ar":"تُعْرَفُ اـِمَّرَتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its decrease;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but the correct meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its increase,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as Fr explains it. (T, TA.) It is said respecting anything of which one knows what is good in it at first sight: (Lh, M:) and means, on a thing's presenting itself, thou knowest its goodness. (T.) One says also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA^aHosana A^amaAratahumo","text_ar":"ماَحْسَنَ اَمَارَتَهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How good is their multiplying, and the multiplying of their offspring and of their number!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA jaEala All~`hu fiyhi A_im~arapF","text_ar":"لَا جَعَلَ اللّٰهُ فِيهِ اـِمَّرَةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God not make an increase to be therein."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","K","S","M","Lh"]},{"entry_id":"n1218","headword_ar":"اَمَرَةٌ","root":"Amr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Stones:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a heap of stones:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or it is the n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amarN","text_ar":"اَمَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stones:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or the latter signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stones set up in order that one may be directed thereby to the right way:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 409:) and the former also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hill;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amarN","text_ar":"اَمَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [used as] its pl.: (M:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark, by which anything is known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaArN","text_ar":"اَمَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaArapN","text_ar":"اَمَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (As, S;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amarN","text_ar":"اَمَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [used as] its pl. in this sense also: (M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark, set up to show the way;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, Fr;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaArN","text_ar":"اَمَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaArahN","text_ar":"اَمَارَهٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark, of stones, to show the way, in a waterless desert;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaArN","text_ar":"اَمَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaArapN","text_ar":"اَمَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark, that is prepared:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a structure like a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaArap","text_ar":"مَنَارَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here app. meaning a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tower of a mosque"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon a mountain, wide like a house"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent, and larger, of the height of forty times the stature of a man, made in the time of 'Ád and Irem; in some instances its foundation being like a house, though it consists only of stones piled up, one upon another, cemented together with mud, appearing as though it were of natural formation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, T:) the pl. (in all the senses above, K) [or rather the coll. gen. n.,] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amarN","text_ar":"اَمَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imorapN","text_ar":"اـِمْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["K","M","TA","ISh","T"]},{"entry_id":"n1226","headword_ar":"اَمَّرَةٌ","root":"Amr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_im~arN","text_ar":"اـِمَّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n1227","headword_ar":"اـِمَّرَةٌ","root":"Amr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_im~arN","text_ar":"اـِمَّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in six places:       -A2-  and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imorapN","text_ar":"اـِمْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n1228","headword_ar":"اـِمّرَةٌ","root":"Amr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imorapN","text_ar":"اـِمْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n38363","headword_ar":"امرّهُ","root":"mr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imoraArN","text_ar":"اـِمْرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, to pass, pass by"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beyond, go, go away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pass away;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb, TA;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a","text_ar":"مَرَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amr~ Al$~iEora","text_ar":"امرّ الشِّعْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He recited the poetry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"especially,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with fluency"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*br","text_ar":"ذبر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amr~hu bihi","text_ar":"امرّهُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in some copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amtr~ bh","text_ar":"امترّ به"},{"kind":"text","text":", but the former is the right reading, TA) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, to pass,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"go, by him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amr~hu EalaY Aljisori","text_ar":"امرّهُ عَلَى الجِسْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him to pass,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"go, along,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over, the bridge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dyke."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amr~ Ealayohi yadahu","text_ar":"امرّ عَلَيْهِ يَدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He passed his hand over him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amr~ Elyh Alqalama","text_ar":"امرّ عليه القَلَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He passed the pen over it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"across it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amorarotu Als~ik~iyna","text_ar":"اَمْرَرْتُ السِّكِّينَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Haloqi Al$~aApi","text_ar":"عَلَى حَلْقِ الشَّاةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I passed the knife across the throat of the sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) It is said in a trad., respecting the sound that is heard by the angels when a revelation is sent down,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA_imoraAri AlHadiydi EalaY AlT~a$oti","text_ar":"كَاـِمْرَارِ الحَدِيدِ عَلَى الطَّشْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Like the dragging,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drawing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in a trans. sense,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the iron over the copper basin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in another trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sawota A_imoraAri Als~ilosilapi","text_ar":"صَوْتَ اـِمْرَارِ السِّلْسِلَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sound of the dragging,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drawing, of the chain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or, accord. to the more common relation,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sawota miraAri Als~ilosilapi EalaY","text_ar":"صَوْتَ مِرَارِ السِّلْسِلَةِ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~afaA","text_ar":"الصَّفَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sound of the dragging,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in an intrans. sense)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and continuous running, of the chain upon the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smooth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rocks:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA:) for ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAr~a","text_ar":"مَارَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miraArN","text_ar":"مِرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dragged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became drawn along."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amr~hu","text_ar":"امرّهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He twisted it tightly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, a rope, (S, A, Msb,) and a thread. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ahoru *uw","text_ar":"الدَّهْرُ ذُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqoDK waA_imoraArK","text_ar":"نَقْضٍ وَاـِمْرَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fortune"},{"kind":"text","text":", as it were,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"untwists and twists tightly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A. TA.) [See art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nqD","text_ar":"نقض"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  Hence also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amr~hu","text_ar":"امرّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He struggled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strove, with him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and twisted about him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twisted his neck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to throw him down;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mAr~hu","text_ar":"مارّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or this latter signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he twisted himself about him, and turned him round, to throw him down;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) [for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yudiyruhu","text_ar":"يُدِيرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the K, we find in the L"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuriyduhu","text_ar":"يُرِيدُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which latter is preferred by SM; but I prefer the former; for it also signifies]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he turned him round,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely, a camel,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order to throw him down:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mAr~hN","text_ar":"مارّهٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he struggled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strove, with him, and twisted his neck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to throw him down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, T, A,) (AHeyth, T, A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the latter desiring to do the same;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the inf. n. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mumaAr~apN","text_ar":"مُمَارَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miraArN","text_ar":"مِرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AHeyth, T:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imoraA^atuhu tumaAr~uhu","text_ar":"اـِمْرَاَتُهُ تُمَارُّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his wife opposes him, and twists herself about him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miraAru","text_ar":"مِرَارُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHrobi","text_ar":"الحرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is explained by As as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the striving to obtain the victory in war."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amr~","text_ar":"امرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imoraArN","text_ar":"اـِمْرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, bitter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, Th, S, M, A, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a","text_ar":"مَرَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Th, S, M, A, Msb, K,) but this was not known by Ks, and Th says that the former is the more common, (M,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Th, M, K,) [whence it seems that the see. pers. of the pret. is both"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marirota","text_ar":"مَرِرْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marurota","text_ar":"مَرُرْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraArapN","text_ar":"مَرَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, K,) or this is a simple subst.: (Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astmr~","text_ar":"استمرّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Sgh, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado A^amar~a ha*aA AlT~aEaAmu fiY famiY","text_ar":"قَدْ اَمَرَّ هَذَا الطَّعَامُ فِى فَمِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This food has become bitter in my mouth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner you say of anything that becomes bitter. (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amar~a Ealayohi AlEayo$u","text_ar":"اَمَرَّ عَلَيْهِ العَيْشُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a","text_ar":"مَرَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Life became bitter to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And Th cites,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"tumir~u EalayonaA AlA^aroDu mino A^ano naraY bihaA\n                     \n                     \n                        A^aniysFA wayaHolawoliY lanaA Albaladu Alqaforu"},{"kind":"text","text":"[(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The land is displeasing to us from our seeing in it man, and the desolate country is pleasing to us"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: the poet makes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tumir~u","text_ar":"تُمِرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"trans. by means of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY","text_ar":"على"},{"kind":"text","text":", because it implies the meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taDiyqu","text_ar":"تَضِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is made trans. by means of the same particle]. (M, TA) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amar~u waA^aHoluw","text_ar":"اَمَرُّ وَاَحْلُو"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amur~u","text_ar":"اَمُرُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA^aHoluw","text_ar":"وَاَحْلُو"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am bitter"},{"kind":"text","text":"at one time,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and I am sweet"},{"kind":"text","text":"at one time. (IAar, M.) [See also 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hlw","text_ar":"حلو"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  But"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^amar~a wamaA A^aHolaY","text_ar":"مَا اَمَرَّ وَمَا اَحْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He said not."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, M,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bitter thing, and he said not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, M,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sweet thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, M.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$atamaniY","text_ar":"شَتَمَنِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN famaA A^amorarotu walaA A^aHolayotu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ فَمَا اَمْرَرْتُ وَلَا اَحْلَيْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one reviled me, and I did not say a bitter thing, nor did I say a sweet thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN maA yumir~u","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ مَا يُمِرُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamaA yuHoliY","text_ar":"وَمَا يُحْلِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one does not injure nor does he profit."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K. *) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amr~hu","text_ar":"امرّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~arahu","text_ar":"مَرَّرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 2."}],"source_refs":["IAth","TA","S","A","Msb","K","M","AHeyth","T","Th","IAar"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}